{"id":"project-LICHEN-k1tb","title":"Partial queue writes on failure not rolled back","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1432-1454 (enqueue_node_sync)
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/adapter.c:1339-1392 (enqueue_static_sync)

When enqueueing multiple messages during config sync:

  for (size_t i = 0U; i < state->emit_count; i++) {
      ...
      ret = enqueue_single_node_info(adapter, &peer_info);
      if (ret < 0) {
          return ret;  // Partial data already in queue!
      }
  }

If enqueue fails mid-way through the loop, partial data has been written to the queue. The require_queue_space() preflight check helps but is not atomic - another producer could consume space between the check and the writes.

The comment at adapter.h:236-243 acknowledges this as 'best-effort degraded semantics' but the behavior could confuse clients expecting atomic config syncs.

Consider documenting the partial-write behavior more prominently or implementing a transaction/rollback mechanism.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:48:46.81878Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:48:46.818814Z"}
